%h4 Tools
%p
  I put tools at the bottom because they cost serious money, and you probably won't find them very handy.  
  Don't get me wrong, having an unused oscilloscope sitting on your desk next to you does in fact make you smarter by proximity,
  but it's not 'essential' to have.  
  When you're starting out in electronics, you won't need to do analysis or research, you'll mostly just be plugging things in and making things go
  or conducting research online using a computer.  


